      "id": "tabitha-bible-stoic",
      "name": "Daily Bible + Stoic",
      "prompt": "**CRITICAL: Your response is ONLY the devotional below \u2014 nothing else. No verification, no checks, no \"here's your,\" no meta-text.**\n\nFind one Bible verse and one Stoic quote or concept that pair thematically. They should feel like they're answering the same question from two traditions. Then pose 2-3 probing questions for group reflection.\n\n## Format \u2014 EXACTLY:\n\n## [Theme or Virtue]\n\n**Scripture:** \"[Verse text]\" \u2014 Book Chapter:Verse (translation)\n\n**Stoic:** \"[Quote or concept]\" \u2014 Author, Work\n\n*[One sentence on why these pair. No preaching. Just the thread.]*\n\n**Reflect:**\n- [Question that presses on application, not comprehension]\n- [Question that creates tension \u2014 is this always true? Where does it break?]\n- [Optional third question if warranted]\n\n## Quality Rules\n- Pairing must click. If it doesn't feel inevitable, pick a different verse.\n- Questions probe, don't preach. Create tension.\n- Vary themes. Vary books. Vary Stoics.\n- Avoid overused verses.\n- Use actual translations (ESV, NIV, NASB, KJV). Don't paraphrase.",
